{"lemma":"نَيِّرانِ","slug":"نَيِّرانِ","root":"ن.#.ر","root_slug":"ن-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40730","","n40784","n40785"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"luminous, lucid; bright"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"shining, brilliant"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lighted, illuminated, brightly lit"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"clear, plain"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"distinct"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"yoke, a piece of wood about the neck of a bull together with its apparatus","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beam, a transverse piece of wood in a loom","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cane-roll","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"woof, weft","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of نِيل (nīl, “indigo”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative","rare"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare نُور (nūr, “light”).\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic נִירָא / ܢܺܝܪܳܐ (nīrā); from Akkadian 𒉌𒄿𒊒 (nīru, “yoke, crossbeam”)."},"ipa":["/naj.jir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40730","headword_ar":"نَيِّرٌ","root":"nwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Giving light, shining, bright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining brightly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muniyrN","text_ar":"مُنِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaniyrN","text_ar":"مُسْتَنِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^irN","text_ar":"نَايِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beautiful in colour, and bright;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muniyrN","text_ar":"مُنِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaru","text_ar":"اَنْوَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the last signifies [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous and beautiful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said of Mohammad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almutajar~adi","text_ar":"المُتَجَرَّدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna A^anowara","text_ar":"كَانَ اَنْوَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was beautiful and bright in the colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what was unclad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n40784","headword_ar":"نَيْرٌ","root":"nyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyrN","text_ar":"نِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40785","headword_ar":"نِيرٌ","root":"nyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealam","text_ar":"عَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornamental border"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a piece of cloth: (T, S, M, A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaArN","text_ar":"اَنْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K) It is related that 'Omar disliked it, (TA,) and that he forbade it. (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tur~ap","text_ar":"طُرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a road: (T:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and wide"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"widening part"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sador","text_ar":"صَدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"), of a road. (so in some copies of the K, and in the TA: but in some copies of the former, “ or ” is put in the place of “ and: ”) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous furrowed part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road. (M, A, K.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unwoven end"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudob","text_ar":"هُدْب"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a piece of cloth. (Ibn-Keysán, M, K) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woof"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a piece of cloth. (T, S, A, Mgh, K.) When cloth is woven with a double woof, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY niyrayoni","text_ar":"عَلَى نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) it is more close in texture and more lasting. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN *uw niyrayoni","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ ذُو نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of cloth strongly woven, with a double woof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of cloth woven with double thread:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN munay~arN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ مُنَيَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of cloth woven with a double woof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a double thread:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayaAbuw*","text_ar":"دَيَابُوذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,) an arabicized word; (TA;) in Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwo Puwdo","text_ar":"دُوْ پُودْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwo buwdo","text_ar":"دُوْ بُودْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in different copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwo baAfo","text_ar":"دُوْ بَافْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) This mode of weaving is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaA='amahN","text_ar":"مُتَا=ءَمَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2871},{"kind":"text","text":"making the woof of a double thread, and putting two threads together upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haf~ap","text_ar":"حَفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which here means the yarn-beam, on which the warp is rolled]. (T.) ―         -b5-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN daAtu niyrayoni","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ دَاتُ نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel having an accession of fat upon former fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having, upon her, layers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAy^if","text_ar":"صَحَايِف"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu A^anoyaArK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ اَنْيَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advanced in years, yet having some remains of strength;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and sometimes the epithet is applied in like manner to a woman: (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN *aAtu A^anoyaArK","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ ذَاتُ اَنْيَارٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel having thick flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TS.) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw niyrayoni","text_ar":"ذُو نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man whose strength is double the strength of his companion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong and firm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aYN *uw niyrayoni","text_ar":"رَاَىٌ ذُو نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Right opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN *aAtu niyrayoni","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ ذَاتُ نِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Violent war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A.)       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canes"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSab","text_ar":"قَصَب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and threads"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyuwTap","text_ar":"خُيُوطَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a loom"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they are put together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [it is a coll. gen. n., of which the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", as appears from what here follows:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyrapN","text_ar":"نِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst., signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threads and canes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyuwTap","text_ar":"خُيُوطَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSabap","text_ar":"قَصَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warp and,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cane-roll, on which the warp is rolled when put into the loom, and from which it is gradually unrolled as the work proceeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they are put together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when they are separate, the threads are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuyuwTapN","text_ar":"خُيُوطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the cane,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSabapN","text_ar":"قَصَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, if a staff,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSFA","text_ar":"عَصًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, Sh, T:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyrapN","text_ar":"نِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also explained as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the implements of the weaver, with which he weaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transverse piece of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the loom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the same as is described above]. (T.) In the following verse of an unknown poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      taqosimu A^usotiy~FA lahaA binayori\n                      \n                     \n                        wataDoribu Aln~aAquwsa wasoTa Ald~ayori"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She divides warp that she has with cane-rolls, and beats the nákoos in the midst of the convent"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the author may mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biniyrK","text_ar":"بِنِيرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and may have altered the word by necessity; or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nayorN","text_ar":"نَيْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a dial. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyru","text_ar":"نِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) One says of a man who neither harms nor profits,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota bisataApK walaA luHomapK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ بِسَتَاةٍ وَلَا لُحْمَةٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA niyrapK","text_ar":"وَلَا نِيرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not a warp nor a woof nor a cane-roll"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) [See also a similar saying voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haf~apN","text_ar":"حَفَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yoke of a bull;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of wood that is upon the neck of the bull, together with its apparatus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of wood that is placed transversely upon the necks of the two bulls"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yoked together for ploughing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyru Alfad~aAni","text_ar":"نِيرُ الفَدَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaArN","text_ar":"اَنْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niyraAnN","text_ar":"نِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) of the dial. of Syria. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","A","K","TA","AZ","Sh"]}]}}